{{notability|Companies|date=July 2015}} '''Arcadia Contemporary''' is a [[contemporary art]] [[Art museum|gallery]] in [[Los Angeles]].
Arcadia Fine Arts Gallery was founded in 1998 by Steve Diamant, showcasing [[Contemporary art|contemporary]], [[Representational art|representational]] artwork.<ref name="pastimesinc">{{cite web|url=http://pastimesinc.com/2011/04/19/arcadia-fine-arts-gallery-interview/|title=Arcadia Fine Arts Gallery Interview &#124; Pastimes for a Lifetime|publisher=pastimesinc.com|accessdate=2014-03-13}}</ref> The gallery changed its name in 2013 to the current title, Arcadia Contemporary.<ref name="fineartconnoisseur">{{cite web|url=http://www.fineartconnoisseur.com/A-Final-Glimpse-of-Arcadia-Fine-Arts-and-a-Preview/17168835|title=Fine Art Connoisseur - A Final Glimpse Of Arcadia Fine Arts And A Preview Of What Is To Come|publisher=fineartconnoisseur.com|accessdate=2014-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313123644/http://www.fineartconnoisseur.com/A-Final-Glimpse-of-Arcadia-Fine-Arts-and-a-Preview/17168835|archive-date=2014-03-13|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> In July 2016 the gallery relocated to Downtown Culver City.
==Articles== *[http://www.highlighthollywood.com/2014/03/arcadia-contemporary-named-best-gallery-in-new-york-2014-highlight-hollywood-exclusive-news/ Arcadia Contemporary Named Best Gallery in New York, 2014] ''Highlight Hollywood Exclusive News'', March 8, 2014 *[http://www.underpaintings.blogspot.com/2013/09/arcadia-gallery-redefining-contemporary.html Arcadia Gallery: Redefining Contemporary] ''Underpaintings'', September 21, 2013 *[https://web.archive.org/web/20140313123644/http://www.fineartconnoisseur.com/A-Final-Glimpse-of-Arcadia-Fine-Arts-and-a-Preview/17168835 A preview of what's to come] ''Fine Art Connoisseur'', July 2013 *[http://www.pastimesinc.com/2011/04/19/arcadia-fine-arts-gallery-interview/ Arcadia Fine Arts Gallery Interview] ''Pastimes for a Liftime, Inc'', April 19, 2011
