The '''Fundación Doctora Clown''' is a Colombian [[Foundation (nonprofit)|foundation]] that works with artists, actors, and musicians to entertain children while they are in the hospital.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url = http://www.redcreacion.org/documentos/congreso7/NNeira.html|title = Sonrisas que curan|date = 2002|accessdate = 2015-03-16|website = Red Creación|publisher = |last = Ninelly Neira|first = Maria}}</ref> It was founded in 1998, and it conducts regular visits to hospitals in [[Bogotá]], [[Bucaramanga]], [[Cali]], [[Cartagena, Colombia|Cartagena,]] [[Barranquilla]], [[Medellín]], [[Pasto, Colombia|Pasto]] and many other cities in [[Colombia]].<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite journal|url = http://www.eltiempo.com/Multimedia/especiales/payasos/ARTICULO-WEB-NOTA_INTERIOR_MULTIMEDIA-12770698.html|title = La doctora Clown y la terapia de la risa|last = Santa Cruz|first = Diego|date = April 30, 2013|journal = [[El Tiempo (Colombia)|El Tiempo]]|doi = |pmid = |access-date = }}</ref>

